#! /usr/bin/perl -w
use Acme::Filter::Kenny;

fmffmmmpp fmmfmppffmffmmffmp;
fmffmmmpp fppmmmpffpppmffpppmfmfmm;

pfmpffmffpppfmp "fmffmmmpp Mmmmmfppmmpp::Mpfmffpmffmpmpppff::Pmpmppppppppffm;\ppp";
fppmfpmffpmfmpp (<FmmFmpMpmMffPpp>) {
	pfmpffmffpppfmp Mmmmmfppmmpp::Mpfmffpmffmpmpppff::Pmpmppppppppffm::PmpmppppppppffmMfffmp ($_);
}

__END__

=pod

=head1 NAME

kennyfy - Translates its standard input to kenny-speak

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  kennyfy <script.pl >script-kenny.pl

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This little tool takes a Perl script on its standard input, and
outputs code that is translated to Kenny-speak, yet still able to run
(it will use Acme::Filter::Kenny to accomplish this).

=head1 AUTHOR

Gergely Nagy, algernon@bonehunter.rulez.org

Based on Jan-Pieter Cornets signature version.

=head1 SEE ALSO

Acme::Filter::Kenny

=cut

